    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
      "name": "Cytillesh Flash",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>The cytillesh patches that grow along the cytillipede's body release a bright flash of blue light that provides bright light in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:20] and raises the light level by one step for the next 20 feet. Creatures within the @Template[type:emanation|distance:40] must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:27] save or become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded} for 1 round and @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Dazzled]{Dazzled} for 1 minute. Creatures within the 20-foot area of bright light that fail this save also become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stunned]{Stunned 4}. The creature can spend an Interact action rubbing its eyes to end the blinded condition. The cytillipede can't use Cytillesh Flash again for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"
        },
